

Share prices on the Taiwan Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday, with the weighted index moved down 25.26 points to close at 6,020.94, according to reports reaching here from Taipei.

The bourse opened at the day's high of 6,063.09 and hit a low of 5,994.91 during trading. A total of 2.75 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover of 73.23 billion Taiwan dollars (2.18 billion US dollars).

Only one of the eight major stock categories gained ground, with paper and pulp issues moving up at 0.2 percent.

Seven of the eight major stock categories lost ground, with banking and financial shares moving down the most at 1.3 percent, followed by construction issues and foodstuff issues both at 0.6 percent.

Plastics and chemicals shares moved down at 0.5 percent, textile stocks at 0.4 percent, and cement stocks and machinery and electronics shares both at 0.1 percent.

Losers outnumbered gainers 560 to 442, with 186 stocks remaining unchanged.

